        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 5 at 6:41PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 638 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northwest of Winifred to 15 miles east
of Denton to 14 miles northwest of Lewistown. Movement was east at
30 mph. In addition to lightning and brief heavy rainfall, wind
gusts in excess of 50 mph have been observed with this storm near
Denton with hail up to one half inch in diameter also possible as
these storms continue east across Fergus county.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lewistown, Winifred, Roy, Fergus, Suffolk, Giltedge, Glengarry,
Heath, Hilger, and Christina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
